com.erudika.para.core

Class App

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.erudika.para.core.App
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Linkable, ParaObject, Votable, Serializable

    public class App
extends Object
implements ParaObject
    This is a representation of an application within Para. This functionality is WORK IN PROGRESS!
    It allows the user to create separate apps running on the same infrastructure. The apps are separated by name and each ParaObject belongs to an app.
    There can be two ways to separate apps - dedicated and shared. Shared apps use their own database table and cache, but share the same search index. Object separation (sharding) is done using the shard key which is usually the same as the appid. Dedicated apps have their own separate database tables and caches and a separate index for each app.
    Author:
    Alex Bogdanovski [alex@erudika.com]
